==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: January
<hw>Jan"u*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Januarius</ets>, fr. <etsep>Janus</etsep> an old Latin deity, the
god of the sun and the year, to whom the month of January was sacred;
cf. <ets>janua</ets> a door, Skr. <ets>y⟦amac⟧</ets> to go.]</ety>
<def>The first month of the year, containing thirty-one days.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Before the adoption of New Style, the commencement of
the year was usually reckoned from March 25.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Janus</ent>⟦br⟧
